begin_memory_text: We talked about who we are, what are jobs was, she told me that she's taken many of these surveys before. We talked about our ages, her neighbor is an electrician
middle_memory_text: WE talked more about where we were from, we're both from up north. WE talked about the ins and outs of my job as an electrician. We talked about her job
end_memory_text: We were looking to see how long we had left, she asked if we could continue the conversation for three more minutes to make sure we hit the time.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going very well especially after this. It was great to have a nice conversation with someone, even if it was a stranger. I'm going to keep this energy up through the rest of the week so that it can impart positive changes over the course of the week.
critical_positive: She let me talk when I wanted to talk, she listened when I talked, and she had unique rebuttals to the things that I said. It went how I imagine all great conversations would go. She was very forthcoming with information and because she was so open, so was I.
critical_negative: The video did lag a couple of times during our conversation but I wouldn't say that negatively impacted the conversation. The lag was only a stutter so it wasn't too bad. There isn't really anything negative I can even say about the conversation at all, there wouldn't even be anything I would change.

begin_memory_text: the first part of our conversation was our names and where we were from. We then moved on to his age and what he did for work and what he was studying.  He is an electrician who is studying electrical engineering.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we discussed where we lived now and where we were from. We talked about what it was like to live in the country and how not having a vehicle impacted us.
end_memory_text: Near the end of the conversation, we talked about health. He and I both get migraine headaches. His mom has lupus. We discussed immune system health. We also discussed his mom's work with AAFES
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to go great. I have been working on my attitude and how I approach life. I have spent most of the past four years languishing from lupus but have had some serious breakthroughs psychologically.  I am starting to build healthy bonds. I plan on spending the rest of this week building more bonds and also resting and giving myself time to relax.
critical_positive: My chat partner was very warm. He was kind and intelligent. He didn't know what to say but he let me lead. He was willing to explore just about anything I had to say and he didn't seem disinterested. If he wasn't interested, I wouldn't know because he was very engaging.
critical_negative: The video worked fine. I think the sound bleeped a couple of times but it wasn't anything that would even register as a technical issue.  I think that my chat partner was a little bit nervous at the beginning as he had some preconceptions about other chats that did not work out for him.
